'''推特'''在许多国家的审查受到推特的批准和支持。在“政府官员、企业或其他第三方用户”投诉的非法推特被成功处理的过程中，推特会通知看不到这条推文的该国用户<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-205_162-57367843/twitters-censorship-plan-rouses-global-furor/ |title=Twitter's censorship plan rouses global furor |date=2012-01-27 |work=CBS News |accessdate=2012-01-27 |agency=Associated Press |archive-date=2012-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128032913/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-205_162-57367843/twitters-censorship-plan-rouses-global-furor/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而在其他情况下，当局可能会采取单方面行动封锁该站点。目前，[[朝鲜民主主义人民共和国|朝鲜民主主义人民共和国]]<ref name="NK">{{Cite web|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/2616449/north-korea-blacks-facebook-twitter-and-youtube/|title=North Korea blocks Facebook, Twitter and YouTube|date=April 4, 2016|publisher=Global News|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|access-date=2016-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406095746/http://globalnews.ca/news/2616449/north-korea-blacks-facebook-twitter-and-youtube/|archive-date=2016-04-06|url-status=no}}</ref>、[[中华人民共和国|中华人民共和国]]<ref>{{cite journal|last=Bamman|first=D.|last2=O'Connor|first2=B.|last3=Smith|first3=N.|date=March 5, 2012|title=Censorship and deletion practices in Chinese social media|url=http://journals.uic.edu/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/3943/3169|journal=First Monday|publisher=University of Illinois at Chicago|volume=17|issue=3|access-date=2013-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211215604/http://journals.uic.edu/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/3943/3169|archive-date=2013-12-11|url-status=no}}</ref>和[[伊朗|伊朗]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=anh.uW3gNZp4|title=Iran Blocks Facebook, Twitter Sites Before Elections (Update1)|date=May 23, 2009|work=Bloomberg|access-date=March 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924183021/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=anh.uW3gNZp4|archive-date=2015-09-24|url-status=no}}</ref>封锁推特。

== 中华人民共和国 ==
{{main|中华人民共和国网络审查}}
推特遭到中国政府的封锁，然而仍然有众多中国网民使用推特<ref name="Bamman">{{cite journal |last=Bamman |first=D |last2=O'Connor |first2=B |last3=Smith |first3=N |date=March 5, 2012 |title=Censorship and deletion practices in Chinese social media. |url=http://journals.uic.edu/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/3943/3169 |journal=First Monday |publisher=University of Illinois at Chicago |volume=17 |issue=3 |accessdate=2013-12-03 |archive-date=2019-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191010160555/https://journals.uic.edu/ojs/index.php/fm/article/view/3943/3169 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2010年，[[程建萍|程建萍]]被判处劳教1年的评论转推建议日货抵制者在[[2010年上海世博会|2010年上海世博会]]期间攻击[[中国2010年上海世界博览会日本馆|日本馆]]。这条推特起初由她的未婚夫发布，他表示这条推特实际上是在讽刺[[中国反日情绪|中国反日情绪]]<ref name="nydailynewscom">[http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2010/11/18/2010-11-18_chinese_woman_cheng_jianping_sentenced_to_a_year_in_labor_camp_over_twitter_post.html Chinese woman, Cheng Jianping, sentenced to a year in labor camp over Twitter post] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2010/11/18/2010-11-18_chinese_woman_cheng_jianping_sentenced_to_a_year_in_labor_camp_over_twitter_post.html |date=20101121051632 }} Aliyah Shahid, 2010 11 18, NY Daily News, 2010-11-18</ref>。

尽管屏蔽了国内对Twitter的访问，但不代表中國对Twitter持抗拒態度，中国一些驻外部门，以及CCTV（中国中央电视台）、环球时报、新华网、人民日报等官媒和观察者网等非官方媒体都使用Twitter、Facebook等社交网络进行对外宣传，扩大国际声誉<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.ifeng.com/travel/news/china/detail_2014_02/14/33807547_0.shtml|title=陕西旅游局上脸书推特开账号 引网友围观|date=2014-02-14|accessdate=2021-08-19|author=南都网}}</ref>。

== 埃及 ==
{{main|埃及网络审查}}
2011年1月25日，[[2011年埃及革命|2011年埃及革命]]期间，埃及民众无法访问推特。一些新闻报道指责埃及政府封锁推特<ref name="Dan Murphy 0125">{{Cite news |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Backchannels/2011/0125/Inspired-by-Tunisia-Egypt-s-protests-appear-unprecedented |title=Inspired by Tunisia, Egypt's protests appear unprecedented |last=Murphy |first=Dan |date=2011-01-25 |publisher=The Christian Science Monitor |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2011-01-29 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5w6N48cuS?url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Backchannels/2011/0125/Inspired-by-Tunisia-Egypt-s-protests-appear-unprecedented |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而埃及最大的移动网络运营商[[沃达丰埃及|沃达丰埃及]]（{{lang|en|Vodafone Egypt}}），澄清这不是他们的行动<ref>{{cite web| url=  https://twitter.com/VodafoneEgypt/statuses/29927017323433984| title=  Twitter / Vodafone Egypt: We didn't block twitter -  ...| publisher=  Vodafone Egypt on Twitter| date=  2011-01-25| accessdate=  2011-01-25| archive-date=  2016-04-14| archive-url=  https://web.archive.org/web/20160414110950/https://twitter.com/vodafoneegypt/statuses/29927017323433984| dead-url=  no}}</ref>。然而，推特的新闻稿并没有说明是哪一家公司承认它们提请封锁<ref name="Alex Sherman">{{Cite news |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-01-26/twitter-says-access-to-service-in-egypt-is-blocked.html |title=Twitter Says Access to Service in Egypt Is Blocked |last=Sherman |first=Alex |date=2011-01-26 |publisher=Business Week |accessdate=2011-01-25 |archive-date=2011-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110129225609/http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-01-26/twitter-says-access-to-service-in-egypt-is-blocked.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，截至1月26日，推特仍无法在埃及访问。1月27日，各大报道声称埃及国内的整个互联网已被关闭<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/01/27/egypt-internet-goes-down-_n_815156.html |title=Egypt's Internet Shut Down, According To Reports |last=Kanalley |first=Craig |date=2011-01-27 |work=Huffington Post |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2011-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307144933/http://www.huffingtonpost.com//2011//01//27//egypt-internet-goes-down-_n_815156.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

互联网关闭不久后，[[谷歌|谷歌]]、[[推特|推特]]和[[SayNow|SayNow]]（1月份被谷歌收购的语音通讯创业公司）宣布启动[[Speak_to_Tweet|Speak to Tweet]]服务。谷歌在官方博客上宣布服务的目标是协助埃及示威者在互联网关闭期间保持联络。用户使用手机发布推特可以留下语音信箱留言，并使用推特标签#Egypt<ref name="Google Blog">{{Cite web |title=Some weekend work that will (hopefully allow more Egyptians to be heard. |url=http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2011/01/some-weekend-work-that-will-hopefully.html |accessdate=2011-05-12 |last=Singh |first=Ujjwal |publisher=Google |archive-date=2011-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110503002907/http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2011/01/some-weekend-work-that-will-hopefully.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。用户只需拨打同一个指定的电话号码，就可以在没有互联网连接的情况下访问这些推文。而接入互联网的用户可以透过访问twitter.com/speak2tweet收听这些推特。

2月2日，埃及四大服务提供商重新建立连接<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-12346929 |title=Egypt internet comes back online |date=2011-02-02 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2019-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413045538/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-12346929 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Egypt Returns to the Internet |url=http://asert.arbornetworks.com/2011/02/egypt-returns-to-the-internet/ |author=Craig Labovitz |date=2011-02-02 |publisher=Arbor Networks |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025112723/http://asert.arbornetworks.com/2011/02/egypt-returns-to-the-internet/ |archivedate=2011-10-25 |deadurl=yes |access-date=2015-07-19 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Egypt Returns To The Internet |url=http://www.renesys.com/blog/2011/02/egypt-returns-to-the-internet.shtml |author=James Cowie |date=2011-02-02 |publisher=Renesys |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110205190100/http://www.renesys.com/blog/2011/02/egypt-returns-to-the-internet.shtml |archivedate=2011-02-05 |deadurl=yes |access-date=2015-07-19 }}</ref>。一个星期后，发生在革命高潮阶段的严格过滤结束。

== 法国 ==
{{main|法国网络审查}}
匿名用户发布反犹太人和种族主义者的帖子后，推特从它的服务中删除了这些帖子。法国宣传组织犹太学生联盟提出诉讼后，2013年1月24日，法官Anne-Marie Sauteraud责令推特透露发布反犹太主义帖子的用户的信息，并指控该帖子违反法国的反对仇恨言论的法律。推特回应称会针对法国的指控“审查其选项”。在每日罚款1000欧元（约合1300美元）的命令生效前，推特有两个星期的时间遵守法庭命令。由于推特在法国没有办公室和员工，存在管辖权问题，所以目前还不清楚法国法庭会如何制裁推特<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/25/technology/twitter-ordered-to-help-reveal-sources-of-anti-semitic-posts.html |title=In a French Case, a Battle to Unmask Twitter Users |last=Pfanner |first=Eric |date=2013-01-24 |author2=Somini Sengupta |newspaper=New York Times |accessdate=2013-01-26 |archive-date=2021-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309033614/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/25/technology/twitter-ordered-to-help-reveal-sources-of-anti-semitic-posts.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.upi.com/Science_News/Technology/2013/01/25/French-court-rules-on-hate-tweets/UPI-38951359153077/ |title=French court rules on hate tweets |date=2013-01-25 |newspaper=UPI |accessdate=2013-01-26 |archive-date=2013-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126104115/http://www.upi.com/Science_News/Technology/2013/01/25/French-court-rules-on-hate-tweets/UPI-38951359153077/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Twitter ordered to give up details of racist tweeters |url=http://www.zdnet.com/twitter-ordered-to-give-up-details-of-racist-tweeters-7000010283/ |accessdate=2013-01-26 |last=Marchive |first=Valéry |work=ZDNet |archive-date=2013-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130128015444/http://www.zdnet.com/twitter-ordered-to-give-up-details-of-racist-tweeters-7000010283/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 印度 ==
{{main|印度网络审查}}
2012年8月[[阿萨姆邦|阿萨姆邦]]暴力事件后，PM0India、Indian-pm和PMOIndiaa等推特账户因欺骗[[印度总理|印度总理]]而遭到封禁<ref name="India targets">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/technology-19343887 |title=India targets social media sites after Assam violence |date=2012-08-22 |publisher=bbc.com/news |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2021-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303105721/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-19343887 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2020年8月開始[[2020－2021年印度農民抗議|印度農民抗議政府通過的新農業法]]，大量示威者在Twitter上討論事件，2021年2月1日[[印度電子信息技術部|印度電子信息技術部]]要求Twitter封鎖250個賬號和推文，Twitter封禁數十個賬號十二小時，包括一些知名人士的賬號<ref>{{cite news |author1=Manish Singh |title=Twitter restricts numerous high-profile accounts in India following ‘legal demand’ [Update] |url=https://techcrunch.com/2021/02/01/twitter-restricts-over-a-dozen-high-profile-accounts-in-india-following-legal-demand/ |accessdate=2021-05-08 |work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |date=2021-02-01 |language=en |archive-date=2021-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526005223/https://techcrunch.com/2021/02/01/twitter-restricts-over-a-dozen-high-profile-accounts-in-india-following-legal-demand/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。之後[[印度電子信息技術部|印度電子信息技術部]]根據《{{link-en|信息技術法 (2000年)|Information Technology Act, 2000|信息技術法}}》69A對Twitter及其高管發出警告，如不處理相關内容將面臨[[有期徒刑|有期徒刑]]和罰款。2月10日，Twitter和印度電子信息技術部召開網上會議，同日印度發佈新聞稿指責Twitter在處理[[2021年美国国会大厦遭冲击事件|2021年美国国会大厦遭冲击事件]]和[[德里红堡|德里红堡]]騷動時有區別對待之疑。隨即Twitter應要求封鎖500個賬號，絕大部分為永久封禁，以防止印度農民抗議等相關字眼（如farmer genocide）出現在Twitter趨勢上<ref>{{cite news |author1=Manish Singh |title=Twitter suspends over 500 accounts in India after government warning |url=https://techcrunch.com/2021/02/09/twitter-takes-actions-on-over-500-accounts-in-india-amid-government-warning/ |accessdate=2021-05-08 |work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |date=2021-02-10 |language=en |archive-date=2021-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606095016/https://techcrunch.com/2021/02/09/twitter-takes-actions-on-over-500-accounts-in-india-amid-government-warning/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2021年4月[[2019冠狀病毒病印度疫情|印度新冠疫情]]惡化，印度要求Twitter和[[Facebook|Facebook]]刪除一些對印度政府處理疫情不力的貼文，印度認為相關言論會製造恐慌<ref>{{cite news |author1=Manish Singh |title=India orders Facebook and Twitter to take down posts critical of coronavirus handling |url=https://techcrunch.com/2021/04/24/india-orders-twitter-to-take-down-tweets-critical-of-its-coronavirus-handling/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+Techcrunch+(TechCrunch)&guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaW5zaWRlLmNvbS50dy8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAEYWe3V2m7ER-6pOfXdIjVIDrfVbS_hLEtNBm5sO-vf1cbIAUi2hLIilSZSJ2oO3Jw2WAY2A3BCPeMSKqpvXoY3kK6Wy669Qtc7R7It5gH6wPLyI8pnjn449qmQp0TmmbCG1YXRUBVstvL_SggplVQINlctf5pWV-BERQcmQDfxx |accessdate=2021-05-08 |work=TechCrunch |date=2021-04-24 |language=en |archive-date=2021-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210510082412/https://techcrunch.com/2021/04/24/india-orders-twitter-to-take-down-tweets-critical-of-its-coronavirus-handling/?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaW5zaWRlLmNvbS50dy8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAEYWe3V2m7ER-6pOfXdIjVIDrfVbS_hLEtNBm5sO-vf1cbIAUi2hLIilSZSJ2oO3Jw2WAY2A3BCPeMSKqpvXoY3kK6Wy669Qtc7R7It5gH6wPLyI8pnjn449qmQp0TmmbCG1YXRUBVstvL_SggplVQINlctf5pWV-BERQcmQDfxx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 伊朗 ==
{{main|伊朗网络审查}}
[[2009年伊朗总统选举|2009年伊朗总统选举]]期间，伊朗政府担心有组织的抗议，封锁了推特<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=anh.uW3gNZp4 |title=Iran Blocks Facebook, Twitter Sites Before Elections (Update1) |date=2009-05-23 |work=Bloomberg |accessdate=2015-07-19 |archive-date=2012-07-21 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120721130810/http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=anh.uW3gNZp4 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2013年9月，推特和Facebook的封锁出于技术错误，在没有通知的情况下被短暂解除，但当天该站点再次被封锁<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://mashable.com/2013/09/16/twitter-facebook-iran/ |title=Iran Unblocks Twitter and Facebook |date=2013-09-17 |work=Chris Taylor |accessdate=2013-09-17 |agency=Mashable |archive-date=2017-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829214714/http://mashable.com/2013/09/16/twitter-facebook-iran/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 俄罗斯 ==
{{main|俄罗斯网络审查}}
2014年5月19日，推特封锁了俄罗斯用户中的亲乌克兰政治账户。这件事发生后不久，一名俄罗斯官员扬言如果推特拒绝删除违反俄罗斯法律的推文，将会完全封锁推特<ref name="ru1">[http://mashable.com/2014/05/19/twitter-blocks-account-russia/ "Twitter Blocks Pro-Ukrainian Political Account for Russian Users"] {{Wayback|url=http://mashable.com/2014/05/19/twitter-blocks-account-russia/ |date=20180215054111 }}, Brian RiesMay, Mashable, 2014-05-19.</ref>。

2014年7月2日，推特封锁了一个属于黑客群体的账户，该账户将克林姆林宫的一些内部文件在互联网上泄露<ref name="ru2">[http://globalvoicesonline.org/2014/07/27/russia-twitter-hackers-b0ltai-censorship/ "Twitter 'Blocks' Access to Russia's Most Infamous Hackers"] {{Wayback|url=http://globalvoicesonline.org/2014/07/27/russia-twitter-hackers-b0ltai-censorship/ |date=20150717072218 }}, Kevin Rothrock, Global Voices Online, 2014-07-27.</ref>。

由於推特公司拒絕響應[[俄罗斯联邦通信、信息技术和大众传媒监督局|俄罗斯联邦通信、信息技术和大众传媒监督局]]的要求刪除貼文，2021年3月10日起，俄罗斯联邦通信、信息技术和大众传媒监督局降低俄罗斯100%的移动设备和50%的固定设备上的推特的运行速度<ref>{{cite news |title=俄罗斯向推特动手：降低在俄运行速度，或将彻底封禁 |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/455228499_120244154}}</ref>。4月2日，俄罗斯莫斯科市一家法庭裁定推特需繳納罚金890万卢布<ref>{{cite news |title=俄法庭宣布对推特处以890万卢布罚款 |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/2021-04/03/c_1127290277.htm}}</ref>。

== 韩国 ==
2010年8月，朝鲜政府开设推特账户后，韩国政府试图封锁推特上的某些内容<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/20/AR2010082005741.html |title=South Korea tries to block Twitter messages from North |date=August 21, 2010 |publisher=Washingtonpost.com |accessdate=2010-09-18 |archive-date=2021-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208101107/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/20/AR2010082005741.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。8月12日，朝鲜推特账户uriminzok（朝鲜语：我们民族之间），在不到一周的时间内吸引了4500名关注者。2010年8月19日，韩国国营通信标准委员会以传播“非法信息”为由封锁该推特账户<ref name="mashable.com">{{Cite web |title=North Korea's Newly Launched Twitter Account Banned by South Korea |url=http://mashable.com/2010/08/19/north-korea-twitter-banned/ |accessdate=2010-09-18 |author=August 19, 2010 Zachary Sniderman View Comments |date=2010-08-19 |publisher=Mashable.com |archive-date=2010-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100824001319/http://mashable.com/2010/08/19/north-korea-twitter-banned/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。据BBC美国和加拿大的消息，专家称朝鲜为了了解如何使用[[社交网站|社交网站]]，已经投资“信息技术超过20多年”<ref name="bbc.co.uk">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-11007825 |title=BBC News – North Korea creates Twitter and YouTube presence |last=Boyd |first=Clark |date=2010-08-18 |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |accessdate=2010-09-18 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308133632/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-11007825 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这对朝鲜这个一直在他们的新闻中发布政治宣传、经常反对韩国并称他们为“战争贩子”的闭锁国家来说，似乎是“一件新鲜事”<ref name="bbc.co.uk" />。尽管只有36条推文，但这个推特账户积累了9000个关注者。截至目前，韩国委员会已下令禁止65家网站，其中包括该推特账号<ref name="mashable.com" />。

== 土耳其 ==
{{main|土耳其审查制度}}
2014年3月20日，法庭下令网络服务应用“保护措施”，推特的访问被封锁。[[土耳其总理|总理]][[雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安|雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安]]在早前的言论中破坏性指控他的小圈子里的[[2013年土耳其腐败丑闻|腐败行为]]后，发誓要“消灭推特”<ref>[http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-26677134 "Twitter website 'blocked' in Turkey"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-26677134 |date=20210130231010 }}, ''BBC News'', 2014-03-20. Retrieved 2014-03-23.</ref>。然而，2014年3月27日，伊斯坦布尔·安那托利亚第18刑事法庭驳回该法庭申请。土耳其宪法法院随后裁定该禁令违法<ref name="Turkey Twitter">{{cite news| url=  http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-26849941| title=  Turkey Twitter ban: Constitutional court rules illegal| publisher=  bbc.com/news| date=  2014-04-02| accessdate=  2014-04-02| archive-date=  2020-11-21| archive-url=  https://web.archive.org/web/20201121091651/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-26849941| dead-url=  no}}</ref>。两个星期后，土耳其政府解封推特<ref name="BBCtrending">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-26876227 |title=#BBCtrending: Turkey's Twitter block 'lifted' |date=2014-04-03 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2014-04-03 |archive-date=2019-06-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619221225/https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-26876227 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。4月20日周日，《[[法兰克福汇报|法兰克福汇报]]》报道推特已经封禁了土耳其两大敌对政权@Bascalan和@Haramzadeler333的账户，两个账户因揭发腐败而知名<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://m.faz.net/aktuell/politik/tuerkei-twitter-sperrt-regierungsfeindliche-konten-12903503.html |title=Twitter sperrt regierungsfeindliche Konten |date=2014-04-20 |accessdate=2014-07-12 |archive-date=2020-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111024602/https://www.faz.net/aktuell/tuerkei-twitter-sperrt-regierungsfeindliche-konten-12903503.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。事实上2014年3月26日，推特宣布在土耳其首次使用国家版主内容工具<ref>{{Cite web |title=Challenging the access ban in Turkey |url=https://blog.twitter.com/2014/challenging-the-access-ban-in-turkey |accessdate=2014-07-12 |date=2014-03-26 |last=Gadde |first=Vijaya |publisher=Twitter |website=Twitter Blog |archive-date=2014-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712032127/https://blog.twitter.com/2014/challenging-the-access-ban-in-turkey |dead-url=no }}</ref>。截至2014年6月，推特在土耳其扣查了14个账户和“数以百计的推文”<ref>{{Cite web |title=Twitter Yasakları: Yolsuzluk, Dedikodu ve Biraz Porno |url=http://www.bianet.org/biamag/diger/156774-twitter-yasaklari-yolsuzluk-dedikodu-ve-biraz-porno |accessdate=2014-07-12 |date=2014-06-28 |last=Sözeri |first=Efe Kerem |publisher=Bianet |website=Bianet |archive-date=2014-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714202100/http://www.bianet.org/biamag/diger/156774-twitter-yasaklari-yolsuzluk-dedikodu-ve-biraz-porno |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 阿拉伯联合酋长国 ==
{{main|阿拉伯聯合大公國人權}}
2015年2月，[[阿布扎比|阿布扎比]]三姐妹在发布推文“我想念我的弟兄”后，遭到阿联酋当局逮捕后失踪<ref name="Amnesty">{{Cite web |title=UAE: Three women held in secret detention over tweets |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/articles/news/2015/02/uae-three-women-held-in-secret-detention-over-tweets/ |accessdate=2015-05-11 |publisher=Amnesty International |archive-date=2015-05-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518091038/https://www.amnesty.org/en/articles/news/2015/02/uae-three-women-held-in-secret-detention-over-tweets/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。三姐妹没能联系到她们的家人或法律代表<ref name="RTFeb15">{{Cite news |url=http://rt.com/news/236295-uae-women-secret-detention/ |title=3 women risk torture in secret UAE detention over 'I miss my brother' tweet – Amnesty |date=2015-02-27 |work=Russia Today |accessdate=2015-05-11 |archive-date=2018-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122005511/https://www.rt.com/news/236295-uae-women-secret-detention/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

据悉，这三名妇女曾和平地宣传他们的兄弟伊萨·苏瓦伊迪的网上竞选。伊萨是2013年所审判的94名持不同政见者中69名被定罪人士之一，该审判被媒体称为“UAE 94”<ref name="Amnesty" />。

